== Preparation ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
#oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into
bite-size pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and
@Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}; set aside.

== Roasted Potatoes and Broccoli ==

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{drizzle}, @Fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}. (For 4 servings, use 2 sheets;
roast potatoes on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

After 10 minutes, carefully toss broccoli on empty side of baking sheet with a
drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} and continue to roast
on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Creamy Honey Mustard Sauce ==

Place sour cream in a #medium bowl{}; add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and turn to
coat.

== Schnitzel ==

Meanwhile, place @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, lemon zest, and
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon} in a large #zip-close bag{}. Season with
@salt{1%tsp}(we used 1 tsp; 2 tsp for 4 servings) and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork.

Pat @pork cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Place sour cream in a medium bowl; add pork and turn to coat.

Place coated pork in bag with panko mixture and seal to close. Shake until
pork is evenly coated.

> You may need to move pork chops around in bag, pressing with your hands, to
> spread out panko and make it stick.

Heat a 1/4-inch layer of @cooking oil{1/4-inch layer} in a large, #heavy-bottomed
pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles
when added to pan, add pork.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cook until panko is golden and pork is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> For thicker pork chops, cook 1-2 minutes more.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

> Cook chicken as instructed or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per
> side.

== To Serve ==

Divide pork, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Serve with lemon wedges on
the side and creamy mustard sauce for dipping or drizzling.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.